{"id":"ev_afa3ef9a91354b4c","runId":"run_252","type":"delegation","at":1782503211888,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_c9868da8870e456a","atom":0,"task":"Atom 1 of Ticket 0067 (migrate legacy flat local/runs/<runId> dirs to ADR-0027 §6 nested local/runs/<workspaceId>/<runId>). This atom is the PURE, TESTED core function only — do NOT wire any caller, daemon, CLI, or perform a real move yet.\n\nWHERE: add the function next to its layout owner in packages/core/src/runner/run-dir.ts (the same file that owns localRunDir/resolveLocalRunDir — keep one owner for the layout). Export it from the package barrels that already export localRunDir/resolveLocalRunDir (packages/core/src/runner/index.ts and packages/core/src/index.ts). Add unit tests to packages/core/tests/run-dir.test.ts.\n\nWHAT TO ADD:\n  export interface FlatRunDirMigrationReport {\n    moved: Array<{ runId: string; from: string; to: string }>\n    skippedActive: string[]\n    skippedUnknownWorkspace: string[]\n    skippedTargetExists: string[]\n  }\n  export function migrateLegacyFlatRunDirs(\n    runsRoot: string,\n    resolveWorkspaceId: (runId: string) => string | null,\n    isActive: (runId: string) => boolean,\n  ): FlatRunDirMigrationReport\n\nBEHAVIOR (synchronous, node:fs):\n  1. readdirSync(runsRoot, {withFileTypes:true}); if runsRoot is unreadable/missing, return an all-empty report (do not throw).\n  2. For each TOP-LEVEL directory entry whose name is treated as a candidate runId:\n     - Use resolveWorkspaceId(entry.name) as the SOLE discriminator of 'is this a legacy flat run dir'. If it returns null, the entry is NOT a known run (e.g. it is a workspace namespace dir like 'cocoder', or an unknown dir) -> record in skippedUnknownWorkspace and leave it COMPLETELY untouched. (Do not move, do not recurse.)\n     - If resolveWorkspaceId returns a workspaceId and isActive(runId) is true -> skippedActive, leave untouched.\n     - Otherwise target = join(runsRoot, workspaceId, runId). If target already exists -> skippedTargetExists, leave the flat dir untouched (NEVER clobber/merge an existing nested dir). Else mkdirSync(join(runsRoot, workspaceId), {recursive:true}) and renameSync(flat, target); push {runId, from, to} to moved.\n  3. IDEMPOTENT: a second run finds no flat dirs left for already-moved runs (they now live nested and are not top-level run candidates because the discriminator on the now-empty flat path won't be hit — flat is gone), so it returns empty moved. Running twice must be a no-op the second time. Make the loop tolerant of entries that are files (skip non-directories).\n\nACCEPTANCE / EXIT CRITERION (scripted): `pnpm --filter @cocoder/core test run-dir` (or the repo's vitest invocation for packages/core/tests/run-dir.test.ts) passes, and `pnpm -w typecheck` (or the repo typecheck) is green. Tests MUST cover: (a) a flat dir with a known active workspaceId is moved to nested and contents preserved; (b) skippedActive when isActive returns true; (c) skippedUnknownWorkspace for a dir the map doesn't know (e.g. a workspace namespace dir 'cocoder' that itself contains a nested run) and that dir is left byte-identical; (d) skippedTargetExists when the nested target already exists (flat left untouched, nested NOT clobbered); (e) idempotency: calling migrateLegacyFlatRunDirs twice yields empty moved on the second call. Use mkdtemp throwaway roots exactly like the existing resolveLocalRunDir test.\n\nMUST NOT BREAK: existing localRunDir/resolveLocalRunDir behavior and their existing tests; do not change resolveLocalRunDir (the compat read-fallback stays — its retirement is out of scope for this atom). Do not touch the daemon, CLI, or any real local/runs data. Keep the function pure of liveness/store knowledge — liveness comes only through the isActive predicate and the runId->workspaceId mapping only through resolveWorkspaceId, so the caller supplies authoritative sources later.\n\nWrite scope: packages/core/src/runner/run-dir.ts, packages/core/src/runner/index.ts, packages/core/src/index.ts, packages/core/tests/run-dir.test.ts."}}
