{"id":"ev_96314bc677ec4f26","runId":"run_252","type":"delegation","at":1782503506485,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_3d0c69b002e24d69","atom":1,"task":"Atom 2 of Ticket 0067 — wire the (already-landed, unit-tested) core function migrateLegacyFlatRunDirs into the daemon so the one-time physical move of legacy flat local/runs/<runId> dirs into local/runs/<workspaceId>/<runId> happens automatically and idempotently at daemon startup, at the proven-safe point where no run is live.\n\nWHERE & DESIGN:\n  1. In packages/daemon/src/launcher.ts add a new exported function `migrateLegacyRunDirsOnce(ctx: OzContext): void` as a SIBLING to `reconcileOrphans` (do NOT fold it into reconcileOrphans — reconcileOrphans owns DB status; this owns dir layout; one responsibility each). It must:\n     - Build the runId->workspaceId map from `ctx.store.listRuns()` (no filter = all runs): const wsById = new Map(ctx.store.listRuns().map((r) => [r.id, r.workspaceId])).\n     - Build authoritative liveness from `ctx.inFlight` ONLY (ADR-0027: live state is OzContext.inFlight, NEVER DB status): const liveRunIds = new Set(ctx.inFlight.values()).\n     - Call the core helper: const report = migrateLegacyFlatRunDirs(ctx.runsRoot, (runId) => wsById.get(runId) ?? null, (runId) => liveRunIds.has(runId)) — import migrateLegacyFlatRunDirs from '@cocoder/core'.\n     - For observability, for each entry in report.moved record a run-scoped event: ctx.store.recordEvent({ runId: entry.runId, type: 'run-dir-migrated', data: { from: entry.from, to: entry.to } }). Do not record events for skipped entries.\n  2. In packages/daemon/src/server.ts call it ONCE at startup IMMEDIATELY AFTER `await reconcileOrphans(ctx)` (the existing comment there already establishes 'the live set is empty here' — that is exactly the safe window). Add a one-line comment tying it to ADR-0027 §6 step 5.\n\nWHY THIS POINT IS SAFE (must remain true): at boot ctx.inFlight is a fresh empty Map and no run process exists yet, so no dir is being written; reconcileOrphans has just flipped any stale 'running' DB rows to 'failed'. liveRunIds is therefore empty and every known flat dir migrates; unknown dirs (e.g. the 'cocoder' workspace namespace dir) and any future in-flight run are skipped by the core function's own logic.\n\nMUST NOT BREAK / CONSTRAINTS:\n  - Do NOT change the core migrateLegacyFlatRunDirs signature or behavior (atom 1, already committed) and do NOT change reconcileOrphans behavior.\n  - Do NOT read DB run.status as liveness — liveness is ctx.inFlight only.\n  - Do NOT move dirs anywhere except via the core helper; no second copy of the move logic.\n  - Keep it synchronous and best-effort: the core helper already swallows an unreadable runsRoot by returning an empty report; do not let migration throw and abort daemon boot (if you are unsure any store/recordEvent call can throw, guard the whole body so a migration failure never prevents the server from starting, and is the only thing that can be skipped).\n\nACCEPTANCE / EXIT CRITERION (scripted): add a daemon test (extend packages/daemon/tests/mutations.test.ts near the existing reconcileOrphans coverage, or a new packages/daemon/tests/run-dir-migration.test.ts) using the existing in-memory store harness (openRunStore(':memory:')) and a mkdtemp runsRoot, that proves: (a) given a committed run (id run_x, workspaceId cocoder) and a flat dir <runsRoot>/run_x with a file inside, after calling migrateLegacyRunDirsOnce(ctx) the dir is at <runsRoot>/cocoder/run_x with the file preserved and the flat path gone, and a 'run-dir-migrated' event was recorded for run_x; (b) when ctx.inFlight has that run (set ctx.inFlight.set('cocoder', 'run_x')), the flat dir is left untouched and no event recorded. The new test plus `pnpm --filter @cocoder/daemon exec tsc --noEmit` (daemon typecheck) and the daemon test suite must be green.\n\nWrite scope: packages/daemon/src/launcher.ts, packages/daemon/src/server.ts, packages/daemon/tests/** (the test file you add/extend)."}}
