{"id":"ev_083a273c418c468a","runId":"run_252","type":"delegation","at":1782503775266,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_d0e03277dda84a9f","atom":2,"task":"Atom 3 of Ticket 0067 — add a runnable end-to-end proof harness that boots the REAL daemon (createOzServer) and proves the ADR-0027 §6 step-5 legacy-flat run-dir migration actually runs on startup. This closes the gap between the unit/integration tests (which call the function directly) and the real boot path (server.ts calls migrateLegacyRunDirsOnce after reconcileOrphans).\n\nWHERE: create scripts/proof-run-dir-migration.mjs, modeled CLOSELY on the existing scripts/proof-workspace-segmentation.mjs (reuse its conventions verbatim: the `probe` string run via `pnpm exec tsx --eval`, a MARKER line carrying a JSON model, the fakeGit()/fakeHost()/okAdapter/controlledIO()/call() helpers, mkdtemp throwaway install root, and the loadModel()+assert()+fail() verifier with a per-objective evidence print). Register it in package.json scripts as \"proof:run-dir-migration\": \"node scripts/proof-run-dir-migration.mjs\" (keep the existing alphabetical-ish ordering near the other proof: entries).\n\nWHAT THE PROOF MUST DEMONSTRATE (positive run):\n  1. Set up a throwaway install home: <install>/local. Open the store at <install>/local/proof.db (openRunStore with an injected monotonic now like the segmentation harness). upsertWorkspace({id:'cocoder', path, name}). Create a completed run: const run = store.createRun({workspaceId:'cocoder', priorityId:'demo'}); store.setRunStatus(run.id,'completed').\n  2. Seed a LEGACY FLAT run dir at <install>/local/runs/<run.id>/ containing a file (e.g. state.json with known contents) BEFORE booting the server.\n  3. Boot the real daemon: oz = await createOzServer({ cocoderHome: install, port: 0, store, git: fakeGit(), sessionHost: fakeHost(), getAdapter: () => okAdapter, io: controlledIO().io, runHeadless: async () => ({exitCode:0, output:''}), restartDaemon: () => {} }). createOzServer runs reconcileOrphans then migrateLegacyRunDirsOnce at startup — do NOT call the migration function directly; the whole point is to prove the boot wiring.\n  4. After boot, assert via the model: <install>/local/runs/cocoder/<run.id>/state.json exists with the original contents; the flat path <install>/local/runs/<run.id>/state.json no longer exists; and store.listEvents(run.id) contains a 'run-dir-migrated' event whose data.from/data.to match the flat and nested paths. Close oz and rm the temp root in finally.\n\nNEGATIVE SELF-CHECK (mandatory, mirror the PROOF_*_INJECT_REGRESSION convention in the segmentation harness header): support an env var PROOF_RUN_DIR_MIGRATION_INJECT_REGRESSION that injects a fault which the migration must catch, so the verifier reports FAIL (process exit non-zero) when set. Implement the injection as: when the var is set (e.g. value 'unregistered'), SKIP registering the run in the store (so resolveWorkspaceId returns null and the flat dir is correctly NOT migrated) while the assertions still demand the nested dir — i.e. the proof's own assertions must fail, demonstrating the check has teeth. The verifier must exit 0 in the normal run and non-zero in the injected run.\n\nACCEPTANCE / EXIT CRITERION (scripted, run BOTH):\n  - `node scripts/proof-run-dir-migration.mjs` exits 0 and prints a clear objective->evidence map (flat→nested move + event recorded).\n  - `PROOF_RUN_DIR_MIGRATION_INJECT_REGRESSION=unregistered node scripts/proof-run-dir-migration.mjs` exits NON-zero (the self-check catches the injected regression).\n\nMUST NOT BREAK / CONSTRAINTS: do not modify any product code (packages/**) — this atom is the harness only; if you find the boot path does not actually migrate, STOP and report it rather than editing product code under this directive. Use only throwaway mkdtemp roots; never touch the real local/runs data. Keep the harness self-contained and dependency-free beyond what the segmentation harness already uses (node:fs/promises, node:http, node:os, node:path, tsx, @cocoder/core, ./packages/daemon/src/index.ts).\n\nWrite scope: scripts/proof-run-dir-migration.mjs, package.json (scripts section only)."}}
